The '1989â90 Football League Cup', known as the Littlewoods Cup for sponsorship
reasons, was the 30th season of the Football League Cup, a knockout competition
for England's top 92 football clubs. The competition name reflects a sponsorship
deal with the Littlewoods.

The competition began on 21 August 1989, and ended with the final on 29 April
1990 at the Old Wembley Stadium. The cup was won by Nottingham Forest who beat
Oldham Athletic one-nil in the final, who regained the trophy after winning it
the previous season. This was the second time that Nottingham Forest had won the
trophy in successive seasons, having won previously in 1978 and 1979. {{infobox
